	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories A Muizenberg woman who went missing on Saturday has been found - alive and unharmed, according to Western Cape police. Angelique Ripepi had been missing for four days before she was reunited with her family on Wednesday. "She was found on Wednesday, alive and unharmed at approximately 18:00, police spokesperson Captain FC van Wyk said. He said a member of the public, who recognised her from flyers, spotted her and alerted the police. Police confirmed that the circumstances relating to her disappearance were under investigation. EWN reported that Ripepi's family said a friend dropped her off at a Table View shopping centre over the weekend, where she apparently had a job interview. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.